<div class="well">
<div class="page-header">
	<h1>Admissions</h1>
	</div>
		<p> Admission into the IT Academy is incredibly simple, it is open to all incoming freshman inside of the Fayette County School District. The only requirement we ask of a student is willingness to learn about technology. Thats it you don't have to be a computer geek or anything, this program is designed to give you an advantage coming out of high school so that you will be prepared for the rapidly increasing IT driven world unlike traditional high school students.</p>
		<div class="page-header">
			<h2>Application</h2>
			</div>
				<p>The Application for the IT Academy is incredibly simple. All it requires is a completed application form that involves a short essay and a Teacher Recommendation from you Middle School. The application and teacher recommendation form can both be downloaded below in the link.
			<div class="page-header">
				<p>
				<h2>Deadlines</h2>
				</div>
					<p>The deadline for applications for the 2014-2015 school year was <strong>October 7, 2013</strong>. Late Application's are still being accepted currently and will be considered on a first come basis. If spots are available, most likely the student will be admitted. If no spots are available they will be placed on a wait-list. Usually many spots open up before the start of the school year so don't give up just because the date has passed. <strong>If you have any questions contact Heather Eppley:</strong></p>
